<BaseLayout title="Our History" description="The story of Future Media — from a single radio station to Namibia's leading media group.">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Our History</h1>
      <p>Two decades of connecting Namibia — one broadcast at a time.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="container page-content__inner">
      <h2>2004 — The Beginning</h2>
      <p>Future Media was founded with the launch of 99 FM in Windhoek, bringing a fresh, youth-oriented radio format to the Namibian airwaves. The station quickly gained a loyal following with its mix of music, talk, and community engagement.</p>

      <h2>2008 — Regional Expansion</h2>
      <p>Radio Omulunga was launched in Oshakati, extending Future Media's reach into northern Namibia. The station became a cultural touchstone for Oshiwambo-speaking communities, broadcasting in local languages and celebrating regional heritage.</p>

      <h2>2012 — Digital & Outdoor</h2>
      <p>Recognising the shift in consumer behaviour, Future Media expanded into digital media and outdoor advertising. The launch of our outdoor division gave advertisers access to premium billboard locations across the country.</p>

      <h2>2016 — One Africa</h2>
      <p>One Africa was launched as a pan-African content platform, combining radio, digital streaming, and live events. The brand became synonymous with contemporary African culture and entertainment.</p>

      <h2>2020 — Sports Division</h2>
      <p>On One Sports was established to cover Namibia's growing sports scene, with cricket, rugby, and football at its core. The division quickly became the go-to destination for sports fans nationwide.</p>

      <h2>2024 — Studio & Production</h2>
      <p>Our state-of-the-art production studio opened at Hyper Motor City, enabling in-house podcast production, video content creation, and branded content at scale for advertising clients.</p>

      <h2>Today</h2>
      <p>Future Media operates as Namibia's most integrated media group, with radio, digital, outdoor, events, and production capabilities under one roof. We continue to innovate and invest in the platforms and people that keep us connected to Namibian audiences.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
